page.title: 01COAST NEAR FILEY
page.content: The block is nearly all sea but includes Filey Brigg (a promontary) and a small stretch of sea front at Filey itself. The seafront is a typical resport promenade to allow tourists access to the beach and at the northern end has a variety of typical seaside facilities, such as cafes and seafood shops, and a pub and amusements. Also here are kept the towns fishing cobles as there is still a small inshore fishing industry based here. The mainstay of the town is tourism as visitors come for the long wide sandy beach and much of the town is geared to cater to tourists. There is a small yatch club and north of the town the land is given over to a country park, a large area of mown grass used as a car park and partially as a caravan site.
